'''Six Jizō''' (六地蔵, Rokujizō)
* Refers to six statues of {{ill|Jizō Bosatsu|ja|地蔵菩薩|12=draft|12=draft}} enshrined together, based on the Buddhist concept of the {{ill|Six Realms of Existence|ja|六道|12=draft|12=draft}}. Also called {{ill|Rokutai Jizō|ja|六体地蔵|12=draft|12=draft}}. ** {{ill|Rokujizō-tō|ja|六地蔵塔|12=draft|12=draft}} – Stone towers carved with six Jizō images on their sides. ** {{ill|Rokujizō-ji|ja|六地蔵寺|12=draft|12=draft}} – A Shingon sect temple in Mito City, Ibaraki Prefecture, enshrining six Jizō Bosatsu as its principal images. ** {{ill|Kyōto Rokujizō|ja|京都六地蔵|12=draft|12=draft}} – A set of six wooden Jizō Bosatsu statues said to have been carved from a large cherry tree by {{ill|Ono no Takamura|ja|小野篁|12=draft|12=draft}} in 852 (Ninju 2). Originally enshrined at {{ill|Daizen-ji (Kyoto)|ja|大善寺 (京都市)|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Rokujizō Village|ja|六地蔵村|12=draft|12=draft}}, they were redistributed during the Hōgen era to six entrance points to the capital by order of {{ill|Taira no Kiyomori|ja|平清盛|12=draft|12=draft}}. ** {{ill|Edo Rokujizō|ja|江戸六地蔵|12=draft|12=draft}} – Modeled after the Kyoto set, these are six copper Jizō statues constructed at various places in Edo between the Hōei and Kyōhō eras. ** {{ill|Kizu no Rokujizō Magaibutsu|ja|木津の六地蔵磨崖仏|12=draft|12=draft}} – Six carved Jizō figures on rock faces in Nishi-ku, Kobe City, Hyōgo Prefecture. ** {{ill|Kōya Kaidō Rokujizō|ja|高野街道六地蔵|12=draft|12=draft}} – Jizō statues established along the Kōya Kaidō route in Wakayama Prefecture during the Edo period. *** First Jizō: Shimizu area, Hashimoto City *** Second Jizō: Minamibaba area, Hashimoto City *** Third Jizō: Shigeno area, Kudoyama Town *** Fourth Jizō: Kawane area, Kudoyama Town *** Fifth Jizō: Sakumizu area, Kōya Town *** Sixth Jizō: Sakurachaya area, Kōya Town ** {{ill|Awa Rokujizō Pilgrimage|ja|阿波六地蔵霊場|12=draft|12=draft}} – A pilgrimage of six Jizō Bosatsu sites in Tokushima Prefecture (Awa Province). ** {{ill|Iyo Rokujizō Pilgrimage|ja|伊予六地蔵霊場|12=draft|12=draft}} – A pilgrimage of six Jizō Bosatsu sites in Ehime Prefecture (Iyo Province). * {{ill|Rokujizō (Kyōgen)|ja|六地蔵 (狂言)|12=draft|12=draft}} – A traditional Kyōgen play titled "Rokujizō."
; Place names in Japan * {{ill|Rokujizō (Nagara)|ja|六地蔵 (長柄町)|12=draft|12=draft}} – A locality in Nagara Town, Chōsei District, Chiba Prefecture * {{ill|Rokujizō-chō (Okazaki)|ja|六地蔵町 (岡崎市)|12=draft|12=draft}} – A locality in Okazaki City, Aichi Prefecture * {{ill|Rokujizō (Rittō)|ja|六地蔵 (栗東市)|12=draft|12=draft}} – A locality in Rittō City, Shiga Prefecture * {{ill|Rokujizō Village|ja|六地蔵村|12=draft|12=draft}} – A former village in Kii District, Yamashiro Province (now Kyoto Prefecture). Associated with six wooden Jizō statues enshrined at {{ill|Daizen-ji (Kyoto)|ja|大善寺 (京都市)|12=draft|12=draft}}, located in Momoyama-chō, Fushimi Ward, Kyoto City. * {{ill|Rokujizō (Uji)|ja|六地蔵 (宇治市)|12=draft|12=draft}} – A locality in Uji City, Kyoto Prefecture. Lies east of Yamashina River in the area historically part of Rokujizō Village. * {{ill|Rokujizō (Toyooka)|ja|六地蔵 (豊岡市)|12=draft|12=draft}} – A locality in Toyooka City, Hyōgo Prefecture
; Stations * {{ill|Rokujizō Station|ja|六地蔵駅|12=draft|12=draft}} – A station located on the border of Fushimi Ward (Kyoto City) and Uji City, operated by JR West, Keihan Electric Railway, and Kyoto Municipal Subway.
