'''Six Jizō''' (六地蔵, Rokujizō)
* Refers to six statues of [[:en:Kṣitigarbha|Jizō Bosatsu]] enshrined together, based on the Buddhist concept of the [[:en:Six Paths|Six Realms of Existence]]. Also called {{ill|Rokutai Jizō|ja|六体地蔵|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokutai Jizō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 地蔵菩薩}}. ** {{ill|Rokujizō-tō|ja|六地蔵塔|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokujizō-tō|qq=}} – Stone towers carved with six Jizō images on their sides. ** {{ill|Rokujizō-ji|ja|六地蔵寺|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokujizō-ji|qq=}} – A Shingon sect temple in Mito City, Ibaraki Prefecture, enshrining six Jizō Bosatsu as its principal images. ** {{ill|Kyōto Rokujizō|ja|京都六地蔵|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kyōto Rokujizō|qq=}} – A set of six wooden Jizō Bosatsu statues said to have been carved from a large cherry tree by [[:en:Ono no Takamura|Ono no Takamura]] in 852 (Ninju 2). Originally enshrined at {{ill|Daizen-ji (Kyoto)|ja|大善寺 (京都市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Daizen-ji (Kyoto)|qq=}} in {{ill|Rokujizō Village|ja|六地蔵村|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokujizō Village|qq=}}, they were redistributed during the Hōgen era to six entrance points to the capital by order of [[:en:Taira no Kiyomori|Taira no Kiyomori]]. ** {{ill|Edo Rokujizō|ja|江戸六地蔵|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Edo Rokujizō|qq=}} – Modeled after the Kyoto set, these are six copper Jizō statues constructed at various places in Edo between the Hōei and Kyōhō eras. ** {{ill|Kizu no Rokujizō Magaibutsu|ja|木津の六地蔵磨崖仏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kizu no Rokujizō Magaibutsu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 木津の磨崖仏}} – Six carved Jizō figures on rock faces in Nishi-ku, Kobe City, Hyōgo Prefecture. ** {{ill|Kōya Kaidō Rokujizō|ja|高野街道六地蔵|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōya Kaidō Rokujizō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} – Jizō statues established along the Kōya Kaidō route in Wakayama Prefecture duri